        "text": "*[Bug 18989] Wishlist: provide conversion of POSIXlt time zone retaining sub-second accuracy*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18989>\n\n--- Comment #6 from Suharto Anggono (<mailto:suharto_anggono@yahoo.com|suharto_anggono@yahoo.com>) ---\n(In reply to Martin Maechler from comment #5)\nClosely related to `c.POSIXlt` are `[&lt;-.POSIXlt` and `[[&lt;-.POSIXlt`, where time\nzone reconciliation was \"inspired\" by `c.POSIXlt` (Bug 18919 Comment 7).\n\n    as.POSIXlt(as.POSIXct(value), tz = tz[1L])\n\ncould become\n\n    POSIXltconv(value, tz[1L])\n\nif `value` is a `POSIXlt` object.\n\nAlso, the test `identical(tz, attr(value, \"tzone\"))` is too strict. Only the\nfirst element of `tzone` attribute matters, and `NULL` is the same as `\"\"`.",
