        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 18191] CMD build fails for packages providing their own VignetteEngine*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18191>\n\nPaul Smith (<mailto:paul@waternumbers.co.uk|paul@waternumbers.co.uk>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |paul@waternumbers.co.uk\n\n--- Comment #4 from Paul Smith (<mailto:paul@waternumbers.co.uk|paul@waternumbers.co.uk>) ---\nCreated attachment 3616\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3616&amp;action=edit>\nProposed change PR18191\n\nFailure seems to be caused by both\n\n``` \nloadVignetteBuilder(pkgdir, TRUE)\n```\nand the subsequent\n\n```\nvigns &lt;- pkgVignettes(dir = '.', check = TRUE)\n```\n\nnot being able to find the package - which at point might not be installed. \n\nThe solution implemented in the patch\n\n- makes sure the package is installed if it is the vignetteBuilder prior to the\ncalls\n- explicitly passed the installation directory to search path in\n`loadVignetteBuilder` and `vigns`\n\nI've tested this by building and checking `startup` and `R.rsp` from source\nwithout previous installation.\n\nIt might be possible to simplify the function logic by removing the second\nensure_installed call that occurs just below the patch in\n\n```\n if (!is.null(vigns) &amp;&amp; length(vigns$docs)) {\n                ensure_installed()\n                ## Good to do this in a separate process: it might die\n```\nbut I'm not confident I understand the logic enough to recommend this.",
